Address: 1/25-27 Enfield Drive St Albans Park VIC 3219
Description:
The Ideal Starter or Investment
As neat as a pin. This property is ideally positioned only a short distance from major conveniences. It offers great potential for an investor, downsizer or first home buyer.
Located at the front of this neat unit complex and consisting of two generous sized bedrooms, both offering built in robes, ceiling fans and quality block-out window furnishings. Adjoining is the spacious living and dining area and overlooking the functional kitchen with extensive bench space and stainless-steel gas appliances.
Completing the floorplan inside is the central bathroom and separate toilet, as well as the full laundry with external access to the outdoor private courtyard. The rear of the home which can be used for entertaining or additional storage space, as well as the bonus of the single lock up garage.
Added features include gas wall heating furnace, carbon monoxide alarm, large open spaces between units and potential rental of $270-290pw. In a handy location, there is loads of scope to invest, move straight in, or to update. Dont miss this opportunity!

Description:
Solid First Home or Savvy Investment
This well-presented, 3 bedroom, 1 bath, brick property set on 590m2 block offers ample parking with an oversized SLUG and side access. This great start home would suit an array of buyers including a young family starting out to a savvy investor with a potential rent of $350 pw approx.
Comprising of neat front entry you'll step inside to find the spacious front living room nicely tiled with large windows allowing in an abundance of natural light, Vulcan gas heating and Kelvinator split system for year-round comfort.
Located off the living area is the updated kitchen offering a 4 burner gas cooktop with rangehood, tiled splashback, double sink, laminated bench tops and ample cupboard space with extra shelving.
Down the hall you will find 3 nicely carpeted bedrooms, the master with built in robes and good sized windows overlooking the neat front yard.
The central bathroom is equipped with corner shower, sunken bath, modern vanity and heat lamps for those chilly mornings, conveniently located off the bathroom is a separate toilet and functional laundry area, which leads to outside.
Outside you will find a secure low maintenance backyard, ideal for children or a four legged friend. Plus a huge side pergola with shade-cloth ideal for summer BBQ's and outdoor entertaining.
This solid property is ideally located next to a park and is a stones throw from Buckleys entertainment complex, nearby sporting ovals, less than 2km to Newcomb SC and 5 mins drive to Geelong CBD.
FEATURES
• 590 m2 block approx
• Kelvinator split system
• Vulcan gas heating
• Rent pw $350 approx.
• Updated guttering
• Solar panel
• Window shutters

Description:
Invest, Collect and Forget!
Light, bright, inviting and immaculately presented, this stunning 3 bedroom townhouse on a corner allotment of approximately 396sqm is perfect for the long term investor looking for a great rental return in a fantastic location or the downsizer searching for the perfect property for the future.
Currently leased at a very attractive $320 per week to long term tenants until October, this stunning home features built-in robes and wall to wall carpet in all bedrooms, a classy mix of polished floorboards and vinyl flooring in the living and kitchen plus high quality fixtures and fittings throughout the home. The beautifully appointed kitchen features stainless steel appliances including electric oven, gas cook top, range hood and dishwasher, island bench and plenty of storage space plus adjoining dining area while the spacious central living room is flooded with natural light and leads out to the private courtyard and entertainment area.
Outstanding extras include ducted heating throughout, reverse cycle heating and cooling and ceiling fan in the living room, quality blinds and light fittings, updated bathroom with separate shower and bath with exquisite tiling and a secure single car enclosed carport. As an added bonus theres also another courtyard with a storage shed and open entertainment area.
Within walking distance to 2 shopping centres, schools, sporting facilities and with easy access to public transport this low maintenance home is perfect for those that dont drive or just want everything that 3219 has to offer at their doorstep and with Newcomb fast becoming the place to buy this is definitely one that you buy for the future!

Address: 26 St Albans Street St Albans Park VIC 3219
Description:
This feels like home...
Step inside and you will immediately feel that cosy feeling of home. Situated in the popular suburb of St Albans Park, where properties on the market are never in an abundance, this cute weatherboard home with front verandah and established gardens certainly has street appeal. Sure to make the perfect choice for families, first home buyers and investors, with an estimated rental income of $400 per week, the convenience is what makes this area so sought after. Only 15 minutes to Geelong CBD and coastal areas, 5 minutes to local shopping centres, local schools and public transport.
Comprising a carpeted formal lounge with reverse cycle airconditioner, updated kitchen/dining with gas cooktop, fanforced oven and glass splashback. The kitchen overlooks the rear yard which will appeal to families with young children.
There are 4 bedrooms, three with built in robes and ceiling fans, 2 with reverse cycle AC. The 4th bedroom has an adjoining walk in robe and ensuite with floor to ceiling tiles, frameless shower and stone top vanity. This 4th bedroom has a sliding door to the rear yard and could also be utilised as a 2nd living room depending on the owner's preference.
The bathroom has also been updated with frameless shower, stone top modern vanity and heated towel rail.
The impressive outdoor area is what makes this home extra special. The decked pergola area has a large 6 person swim spa , ideal for entertaining, hydrotherapy and keeping fit all year round. There is also a private lawn area with ample room for children to play. Allotment approximately 589sqm.
The side drive leads to a huge steel double garage with roller door, mezannine floor for extra storage and a home office with AC and ceiling fan, making it perfect for someone wanting to work from home. This area would also be perfect for the home handyman or as a teenager's retreat.
Don't delay your enquiries on this one, it really does have it all!

Description:
BRILLIANT BREAKWATER
This newly updated 3 bed 1 bath 1960's brick property would make a fantastic first home with room to move set on 690m2 block or would be a savvy investment with a potential rent of $370pw.
Located in growing pocket of Breakwater and offering a wonderfully sized backyard with views across to South Geelong, this home is a must to inspect.
Step foot inside to find a neat and tidy newly painted and carpeted home. The large light filled living room is equipped with ceiling fan and gas heater which was recently serviced, for all year round comfort. This room flows beautifully onto the kitchen meals area which easily accommodates up to 6 people and the kitchen has been tastefully done in a neutral colour palate. It also offers wonderful night views of Belmont Hills lights and is equipped with new splash back, electric cooking and ample new bench space.
Down the hall you will find 3 generous sized bedrooms two with BIR and master with ceiling fan and a leafy front garden outlook.
The central bathroom has been newly updated in fresh white with all new tap fittings. It offers bath, updated shower and new vanity storage unit plus a separate toilet.
There is a handy sunroom extension located towards the rear of the home for all year round outdoor entertaining or summer BBQ's.
Outside is a great size back yard ideal for children or your four legged friend and a DLUG which could easily make for an ideal workshop or storage shed as the long driveway caters for ample off street parking up to 2-3 cars.
This solid great start property is ideally located 5 minutes drive over the bridge to Belmont Shops, less than 20 mins drive to nearby coasts or less than 5 km to Geelong CBD.

Calling all first home buyers, growing families and Investors
Set on approximately 652m2, this well presented freshly painted, and thoughtfully cared for 3 bedroom brick veneer home will impress the most discerning occupier or astute investor.

Comprising of three good sized bedrooms, all with built in robes, and easy access to the new renovated family bathroom incorporating a bath, shower and separate toilet. Stepping through the glass sliding door from the dining area leads you to a lovely undercover alfresco area facing the expansive north facing backyard with 2 garden sheds.

The standout feature of this property is the huge side area accessible through double gates making this property suitable for caravan or boat storage - or both!

With an approximate rental of $370pw, and minutes from local schools, Newcomb Shopping Village, Splashdown Aquatic Centre and Geelong CBD, you'll need to be quick to inspect this quality home in one of Geelong's most popular areas.

Description:
Rare Find In The Heart Of East Geelong
Location, presentation and space; this one ticks all the boxes. Set on a private allotment of approximately 475 square metres with north facing backyard and rear lane access. This beautiful example of traditional elegance combined with modern style is perfect for any astute buyer searching for a genuine family home in an unsurpassed location.
Among the outstanding features of this classic home is the versatile floor plan with all 3 bedrooms generous in size and featuring high ceilings, exquisite polished Baltic pine floorboards, built-in robes and an ornate fireplace in the master bedroom plus light fittings that complement the home perfectly. The open plan kitchen, dining and living area has been cleverly designed to allow an abundance of natural light to flow through and the beautifully appointed kitchen is complete with stainless steel oven, cook top and range hood plus dishwasher and plenty of storage and bench space. The central bathroom is functional in design and has a separate bath and shower and neutral tiling with classic fittings.
The centrepiece of this stunning home has to be the second living area that opens out to the north facing deck and spacious rear yard. Ideal for entertaining family and friends all year round and able to be zoned off from the rest of the house with French doors to accentuate the feeling of space and light right through the rest of the home. The sizeable deck area is completely covered and overlooks a large north facing yard that has plenty of foliage for extra privacy and enough space to swing a cricket back or even add a swimming pool.
The large multipurpose three room garage, workshop and storage building, complete with roller door to the rear lane, provides unlimited opportunity.
Outstanding extras include ducted heating throughout the home, reverse cycle heating and cooling in second living room, ornate cornices and architraves, updated window furnishings, extra shelving, second toilet and storage in the laundry.
Only minutes walk from the botanical Gardens, East Geelong shops, Geelong C.B.D, St John of God and Geelong hospital, South Geelong train station, Geelong Waterfront and GMHBA stadium, this is the ultimate lifestyle property and with the impressive infrastructure improvements happening in and around the Geelong area its no wonder why it is such high demand. Dont waste time thinking about, make an appointment today!

Description:
DESIGNED FOR EASY LIVING
PLEASE CONTACT US TO REGISTER FOR OPEN INSPECTIONS
Low-maintenance living has never been easier than with this neat-as-a-pin, three-bedroom home less than 5 minutes from Geelongs CBD.
Perfectly positioned on the fringe of East Geelong and close to shops and schools, this weatherboard home is an ideal fit for a young family, down-sizers or a corporate couple.
Space has been a priority in this clever design, which boasts a large lounge, separate dining area, kitchen with loads of bench and storage options, plus two decks for alfresco entertaining or simply relaxing outdoors.
The three generous light-filled bedrooms, two with built-in robes, are serviced by a central family bathroom.
Other highlights of the property include rear double carport with security door, storage area, secure fenced and low-maintenance yards, split-system heating and cooling unit, laundry with generous bench space, plus second toilet.
The home is a few minutes drive to Bellarine Village and Newcomb Central shopping centres, as well as Newcomb Secondary College, Geelong High School and Christ the King and Newcomb Park primary schools.
It is also within easy reach of Geelongs University Hospital and Geelong railway station for commuters to Melbourne, while buses to the CBD run nearby.
And for beach lovers, the highway to the Bellarine Peninsula is right on your doorstep.

Address: 31 East End Crescent St Albans Park VIC 3219
Description:
Great value for money
Situated in a quiet street, 5 minutes to local shopping centres and schools, 10 minutes to Geelong CBD and 15 mins to coastal areas, this convenient location is sure to suit both owner occupiers and investors, with a potential rental income of $380 per week. Being on a large allotment, this property also has the potential for subdivision or redevelopment STCA.
Comprisng L-shaped lounge/dining with a wood heater to keep cosy during the cooler months, updated kitchen/meals with stainless steel gas cooktop and electric oven. This area has a gas wall furnace for heating and glass sliding doors opening out to the entertaining area, perfect for combined indoor/outdoor entertaining.
There are three good sized bedrooms all with built in robes, master with double BIRS and adjoining 2-way bathroom. This updated bathroom provides a separate bath and shower and modern vanity. Outdoors is a large undercover pergola, extensive rear yard, storage shed and single drive through garage. Allotment approximately 726sqm.

Address: 31 St Albans Road East Geelong VIC 3219
Description:
TOWNHOUSE LIVING IN THE HEART OF EAST GEELONG
This spacious 2 bed,1 bath, large living townhouse in a prime pocket of East Geelong would suit an array of buyers including FHB, a professional worker offering low maintenance living or a savvy investor with a potential rent of $350 pw and a lease in place until Sept 2020.
Set in a group of only 4, this 2 storey property comprises of an open plan design featuring large light filled living space downstairs, an updated Kitchen equipped with built in cabinetry and pantry, modern splash back, a 4 Burner gas Westinghouse cooktop, hidden draw dishwasher and modern island bench which accommodates up to 3.
Towards the rear of the home you will find a handy laundry space and downstairs toilet.
Follow the wooden staircase up to the second level to find a central bathroom with shower over bath, IXL heat lamps for those chilly mornings and 2nd seperate toilet.
The 2 upstairs bedrooms are a fantastic size and both offer blockout blinds, BIR and views back over St Albans rd.
Outside you will find a secure front deck and garden ideal to relax or entertain plus a neat back courtyard, storage room and SLUG.
This quality investment, first home or ideal downsizer is conveniently located close to South Geelong train station, Local parks and 5 mins walk to Eastern Beach Geelong.
FEATURES :
Rent pw $350 apx lease sep 2020
Body Corp $600pa apx
SLUG w rear lane access
Breeze Air AC/Heating
Rinnai Gas Heater
2 Toilets
